Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.11,0:02:02.73,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a beautiful view!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.29,0:02:06.79,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We sure were lucky! I was worried for a while there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.79,0:02:07.87,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.87,0:02:11.69,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He forgot what time our return ship left,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.69,0:02:14.42,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,so we got to ride on this big one instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:19.36,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was a good thing this ship just happened to stop at the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:23.57,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We would've been stranded out there for three days if it hadn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.57,0:02:28.20,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I wonder what kind of people would reserve a ship like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.21,0:02:36.84,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.23,0:02:40.96,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.46,0:02:44.98,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking about my parents who died in an accident last year...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.15,0:02:48.82,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wish they could've seen me all dressed up today...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.41,0:02:50.53,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All dressed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:52.73,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong, Natsue?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.33,0:02:54.25,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.10,0:02:57.66,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The two of us were married today!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.35,0:02:59.74,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Married?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:05.39,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shoichi's 2nd daughter\NNatsue Hatamoto (22)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:05.39,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Natsue's Husband\NTakeshi Hatamoto (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.74,0:03:02.88,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We had our ceremony this morning on Hatamoto Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.88,0:03:05.42,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,the same island you were on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.69,0:03:07.98,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.68,0:03:11.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But why did you have it on the island?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:16.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The majority of the island belongs to the Hatamoto family.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.10,0:03:18.62,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We honor generations of our ancestors there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.62,0:03:23.58,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Hatamoto family tradition to hold wedding ceremonies on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:26.00,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.95,0:03:32.37,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We reserved this boat for ourselves, so what are strangers doing on it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.37,0:03:34.33,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.33,0:03:37.18,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They appeared to be stranded, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.35,0:03:40.13,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you go over my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.37,0:03:46.26,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You must think pretty highly of yourself if you're making decisions without approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.22,0:03:47.56,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mariko's husband\NKitaro Hatamoto (47)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.22,0:03:47.56,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Head of the Hatamoto family\NGo Hatamoto (72)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.26,0:03:48.05,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, of course I don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.56,0:03:50.05,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.05,0:03:53.90,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's been in a bad mood since the ceremony today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.90,0:03:56.90,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, after he ate my food...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.90,0:03:58.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Joji-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.10,0:04:02.90,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I knew he hated Western-style food,\Nbut I had no idea he'd get that angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.90,0:04:05.20,Flashback,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You call this food?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.71,0:04:11.71,Character Card,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(500,500)}Second son of the\NHatamoto family\NJoji Hatamoto (41)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.84,0:04:08.90,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It seems my skills still aren't up to par.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.90,0:04:10.57,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.57,0:04:12.32,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was really delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.32,0:04:16.12,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, lady-killer... What's with the flower on your chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.12,0:04:20.47,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Natsue put it there on the way back from the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.47,0:04:23.78,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's always been my dream since I was a little girl
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:28.20,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,to give my beloved this flower that only grows on that island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.18,0:04:32.60,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Kitaro's only son\NIchiro Hatamoto (21)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.55,0:04:30.20,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad it wasn't me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.57,0:04:36.15,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like father, like son!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.15,0:04:39.41,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you going to let him to pretend to be an artist?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.41,0:04:41.98,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're his father, talk some sense into him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.98,0:04:44.52,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him to give up his hopeless dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.52,0:04:45.61,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.36,0:04:47.61,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:49.01,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.01,0:04:52.44,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I need a word with you! Come to my room later!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.44,0:04:53.63,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.47,0:04:58.71,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just have patience, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.38,0:05:03.61,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't long for this world—\Nhe'll be gone soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.92,0:05:10.72,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eldest Hatamoto daughter, Kitaro's wife\NMariko Hatamoto (43)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.54,0:05:10.95,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And when he is, nearly all of the Hatamoto fortune will be yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.95,0:05:14.66,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be so sure about that, Aunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.53,0:05:16.75,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed to mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.24,0:05:19.91,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Akie-{\i1}san{\i0}! Do you know something I don't?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:22.65,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shoichi's daughter &\NNatsue's sister\NAkie Hatamoto (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.44,0:05:23.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be {\i1}too{\i0} shocked when you hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.34,0:05:30.44,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible! That can't be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.44,0:05:33.22,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like Grandfather's going to make the announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.22,0:05:34.66,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,when we get back to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.64,0:05:37.75,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.24,0:05:40.25,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Akie's husband\NTatsuo Hatamoto (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:41.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Does he even know we're up to our necks in debt over here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.39,0:05:45.80,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We have 24 hours until the ship arrives in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.80,0:05:49.35,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We simply {\i1}have{\i0} to do something before then...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.00,0:05:59.90,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Takeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.90,0:06:00.80,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.40,0:06:05.30,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to disturb you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.50,0:06:10.06,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was an exceptional speech you gave at the wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.06,0:06:12.61,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just what I would expect of the man whom Natsue chose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:15.28,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.21,0:06:19.39,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Scratching your cheeks when you're embarrassed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:20.68,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're just like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.75,0:06:24.52,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just like your father, Isao Zaiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.35,0:06:29.30,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Falsify your family registry all you want, you still cannot fool me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.77,0:06:33.25,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've known all this time that you joined the company
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.25,0:06:37.25,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and got close to Natsue just to avenge your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.90,0:06:40.61,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is it you're after?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.21,0:06:42.12,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Money?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.04,0:06:45.51,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or my life, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:48.92,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter? Why won't you speak?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:51.06,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.35,0:06:56.72,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,These are the main members of the Hatamoto family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.89,0:07:00.74,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So all of these people went to your wedding, Natsue-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.29,0:07:03.72,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! All nine of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.72,0:07:06.33,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,excluding my late parents Shoichi and Miyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.04,0:07:09.85,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0} is rather late...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.85,0:07:13.15,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He still hasn't come back from Grandfather's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.15,0:07:14.54,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:18.29,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're discussing some under-the-table business!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.84,0:07:20.05,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.41,0:07:27.25,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.25,0:07:28.51,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.11,0:07:31.59,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dad not here yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.83,0:07:35.33,Signs,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hatamoto family butler\NKenji Suzuki (64)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.22,0:07:35.47,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, though I am certain he will be here shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.95,0:07:37.86,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're late, Ichiro-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.86,0:07:39.28,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you make sure to wash your hands?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.28,0:07:40.06,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:43.33,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say! Do you have a boyfriend, Ran-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:48.38,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not, she's still a kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.38,0:07:49.62,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.95,0:07:52.09,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have you know there {\i1}is{\i0} someone I like!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.56,0:07:53.89,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:55.70,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:58.40,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.32,0:08:05.36,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's really smart, good at soccer, dependable, and cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.15,0:08:09.05,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are {\i1}you{\i0} acting so embarrassed about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.51,0:08:12.53,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And he's an even better detective than my dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.40,0:08:15.39,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You mean your father's a—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:17.39,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? I didn't tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:19.39,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My dad's a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.17,0:08:29.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.84,0:08:33.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it a secret from my grandfather! He hates detectives!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.18,0:08:36.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He says that people who pry into others' affairs are despicable!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.88,0:08:40.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's right, at least in old man Kogoro's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.58,0:08:44.97,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sir? Your seat is ready, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.28,0:08:48.28,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A flower?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.68,0:08:55.22,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}! You're really late!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.05,0:08:59.61,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I was thinking about some things in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.15,0:09:02.56,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alright? You look pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.11,0:09:06.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What happened to the flower on your chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.12,0:09:09.16,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. Where could I have lost it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.76,0:09:13.99,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to disturb you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.99,0:09:15.51,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is waiting for you—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.87,0:09:19.32,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Whose voice was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.32,0:09:20.45,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The butler Suzuki's!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.45,0:09:21.57,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It came from Dad's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.69,0:09:26.00,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What happened, Suzuki-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.13,0:09:39.17,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late. He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.17,0:09:40.19,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.19,0:09:41.21,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,- Grandfather!\N- Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.90,0:09:43.21,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone stay out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.65,0:09:47.08,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's to enter this room until I say it's OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.38,0:09:55.41,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that 40 or 50 minutes have passed since Mr. Gozo's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.40,0:10:00.17,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who found him, Suzuki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.17,0:10:00.90,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.83,0:10:06.82,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you 40 to 50 minutes ago, around 8:00 PM?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.31,0:10:11.00,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was getting things ready for dinner at 8:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.00,0:10:12.71,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,so I was in the dining room the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.71,0:10:17.54,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}did{\i0} see Suzuki-{\i1}san{\i0} working in a hurry around the tables!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.28,0:10:22.97,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The door to this room was locked when you found the body, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.97,0:10:23.76,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:26.02,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What ways are there to lock the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:27.66,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It can be locked from the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.66,0:10:30.17,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,but you need this key to lock it from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:35.80,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And this window doesn't open, so it's impossible to sneak into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.80,0:10:39.75,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this room was impregnable!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.75,0:10:41.45,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Impregnable?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.45,0:10:44.02,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that my grandfather committed suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.80,0:10:46.34,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.34,0:10:50.83,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If it {\i1}was{\i0} a suicide, then there's something important missing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.60,0:10:54.24,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.24,0:10:57.78,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He died of blood loss after being stabbed in the abdomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.78,0:11:01.31,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But the knife used to do it is nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.31,0:11:04.25,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it wasn't a dagger made of ice or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.25,0:11:07.95,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mystery novels are full of things that melt away and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.95,0:11:11.07,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Would someone seriously commit suicide with something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.74,0:11:13.74,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I bet this is more of his harassment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.55,0:11:18.85,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to torment us by making every Hatamoto here seem suspect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.21,0:11:22.51,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He hated everyone in the family, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.87,0:11:25.62,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone except Natsue, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.21,0:11:27.40,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:29.98,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't put it past the old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.98,0:11:32.85,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's decided! It was a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.85,0:11:34.05,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.05,0:11:34.94,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.94,0:11:36.94,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And an extremely simple one, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.32,0:11:39.28,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.28,0:11:42.30,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here, take a close look at the doorframe!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:44.64,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See the blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.17,0:11:48.74,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If the door was closed when he committed suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.74,0:11:50.87,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,none of his blood could have landed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.59,0:11:56.05,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So it's more natural to think that he was stabbed while the door was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:12:02.38,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Somebody stabbed Mr. Gozo the instant he left the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.38,0:12:04.55,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then who locked the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.78,0:12:07.45,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No clue...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.45,0:12:09.66,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you sure you're a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:22.03,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! It was Mr. Gozo himself who locked the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.43,0:12:26.49,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Someone stabbed him outside the room and then kept coming for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.49,0:12:31.18,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,so he locked himself inside to escape his attacker!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.18,0:12:33.87,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But then he ran out of strength and died!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.87,0:12:36.50,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That would make the most sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.05,0:12:39.56,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a great detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:46.55,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! That means everyone had an opportunity to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.55,0:12:48.95,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The murder took place at approximately 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:53.42,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, Conan, Natsue-{\i1}san{\i0}, and I were at our table since 7:30,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.42,0:12:54.67,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,so none of us could have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.94,0:12:59.15,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The same can be said for Suzuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, who was near our table at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.00,0:13:03.56,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, since the killer wasn't in the dining room at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.32,0:13:08.06,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...it was one of you seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.97,0:13:15.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:18.96,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When you entered the room, did you notice anything out of the ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:21.13,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing in particular...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.13,0:13:25.08,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, now that you mention it, I found this flower in front of the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.50,0:13:26.22,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Flower?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.38,0:13:31.70,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's the flower I put on Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s jacket!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.49,0:13:38.53,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you were really late coming to the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.18,0:13:42.61,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, Sis, I was just thinking about things in my room...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.61,0:13:45.36,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try to deny it, Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.12,0:13:52.51,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to hear you and Father shouting in his room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.35,0:13:57.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was going to faint
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.03,0:14:02.79,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,when I heard that you're actually the son of Isao Zaiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.29,0:14:09.77,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this Isao Zaiki?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.65,0:14:17.83,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He committed suicide when Gozo took over his company, Zaiki Industries, 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.56,0:14:22.76,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One year later, his wife died of an illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.76,0:14:27.25,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and their only son was apparently placed in an institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:30.64,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To think that that was Takeshi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.07,0:14:32.94,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true, Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.62,0:14:34.94,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.75,0:14:41.13,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm Takehiko Zaiki, son of Isao Zaiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:45.95,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I... I...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.39,0:14:50.53,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...got close to Natsue-{\i1}san{\i0} so you could avenge your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.91,0:14:53.16,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You decided to become a member of the Hatamoto family
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.16,0:14:56.49,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,and wait for the chance to kill Mr. Gozo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.83,0:15:00.28,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then tonight, you did just that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.44,0:15:03.76,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! I didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.72,0:15:08.06,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Natsue! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.26,0:15:12.97,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I had you pegged as a pretty staunch fellow,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.97,0:15:15.41,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,but it looks like I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.41,0:15:16.44,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Joji-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.94,0:15:19.94,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be an idiot to drop your flower at the crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.94,0:15:22.38,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't, I lost my flower somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.26,0:15:25.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There are wiped blood stains on the outside carpet...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.41,0:15:29.54,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Say, was that flower really here on the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.54,0:15:31.75,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.11,0:15:35.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.19,0:15:39.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A bread crumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:42.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A bread crumb lying in a pool of blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:44.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's it mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.73,0:15:46.67,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Say, Mr. Butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.70,0:15:52.70,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Was there bread during the wedding banquet this afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.70,0:15:57.08,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But of course—it was an extravagant French meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.08,0:16:02.27,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Joji-{\i1}sama{\i0} made it all himself.\NHe runs his own French restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.70,0:16:04.22,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did everyone eat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.22,0:16:06.93,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Everyone but the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.93,0:16:09.31,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He loathed Western-style food.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.31,0:16:13.72,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said that just looking at bread would make him nauseous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.72,0:16:17.77,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If Joji-{\i1}san{\i0}'s a chef, he has kitchen knives of his own, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:21.20,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally. Chefs like him always own their own set.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.24,0:16:26.30,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come now, children shouldn't pry into other people's business.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.45,0:16:30.51,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:33.20,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cool off in this storeroom for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.55,0:16:35.39,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Open up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.39,0:16:37.97,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it! I didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.23,0:16:40.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid, you murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.23,0:16:43.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're giving you to the police the minute we arrive in Tokyo tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.24,0:16:45.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Better get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:49.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His motive and all the evidence is more than enough, right, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.48,0:16:51.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had more than enough motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.34,0:16:56.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if his fingerprints are found on the murder weapon, it's in the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.69,0:16:57.72,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.72,0:16:58.59,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.69,0:17:00.87,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.46,0:17:02.56,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.14,0:17:05.32,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are lucky, Aunt Mariko-{\i1}sama{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.92,0:17:08.81,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now that Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0} has killed the old man,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.81,0:17:12.54,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,he'll never make that stupid\Nannouncement about his inheritance!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.99,0:17:14.81,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.31,0:17:17.25,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now the Hatamoto Group will belong to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.25,0:17:19.90,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,the husband of his eldest daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.84,0:17:23.18,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you can draw as much as you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:24.42,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,now that your grandfather's dead, Ichiro-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.11,0:17:28.46,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And eventually, you too will become the Hatamoto Group's—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.46,0:17:31.04,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really want that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.38,0:17:35.68,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you ain't thinkin' of monopolizing the guy's inheritance, are ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.68,0:17:38.84,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! All you grandchildren will get—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.84,0:17:43.16,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, could you not talk about money on the night of our father's death?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.46,0:17:48.55,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you to talk? You left the family to go be a chef!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.12,0:17:50.87,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know that Father flat out refused you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.61,0:17:56.62,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,when you asked to borrow money for your restaurant!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.59,0:18:02.68,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted his money too! So be grateful!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.68,0:18:03.81,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.18,0:18:07.08,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm extremely sorry to say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.08,0:18:09.97,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,but the master wrote up a will
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.97,0:18:14.13,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,just in case something was to happen to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.13,0:18:15.41,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.41,0:18:19.87,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it will be read at the main office in the next few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.10,0:18:21.52,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.52,0:18:22.76,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,—all of his fortune goes to—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.89,0:18:25.35,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Natsue?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.11,0:18:26.86,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.86,0:18:30.07,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And leadership of the Hatamoto Group is to be given to the man
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.07,0:18:31.48,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,that Natsue-{\i1}sama{\i0} chose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.48,0:18:33.97,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.97,0:18:39.04,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What? Then what the hell did I marry Akie for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.66,0:18:43.21,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you only married me to get my dad's money!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.21,0:18:48.69,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Why else would I live with a tight-fisted bitch like you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.91,0:18:51.85,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you to talk?! You're just a worthless musician!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.85,0:18:53.37,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Go and get a real job!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.14,0:19:02.01,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Natsue-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.91,0:19:05.42,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.49,0:19:09.83,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, just thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.26,0:19:13.69,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,About Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:18.62,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I trusted him...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.47,0:19:21.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I trusted Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.19,0:19:28.73,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But he only married me so he could kill my grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.37,0:19:32.71,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never trust anyone again!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.14,0:19:40.71,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.04,0:19:48.29,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My gut feeling tells me that he's not a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.83,0:19:50.91,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one you chose, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.53,0:19:53.43,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't possibly be a bad person!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.81,0:19:55.67,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.90,0:20:00.01,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:04.53,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you hear anything strange just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.66,0:20:07.29,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear anything, Natsue-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.29,0:20:09.05,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.05,0:20:10.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No, I did hear something!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.30,0:20:13.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The sound of something falling into the water
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.09,0:20:15.93,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and then a weird thud from the deck below!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.75,0:20:18.79,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.41,0:20:21.80,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.19,0:20:28.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's gotten into you two—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.84,0:20:39.41,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of death was most likely brain damage
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.41,0:20:41.41,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,caused by a blow to the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.71,0:20:43.00,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the wound,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.00,0:20:45.83,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,the murder weapon was a steel pipe or something similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.83,0:20:48.72,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who would do something this terrible?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:50.69,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me Takeshi's struck again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.03,0:20:53.11,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible. He was locked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.11,0:20:55.37,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.24,0:21:00.39,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The door's unlocked!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.39,0:21:01.11,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.09,0:21:05.97,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.34,0:22:43.98,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't in the storeroom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.98,0:22:48.21,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We most certainly locked him inside, but he's nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.58,0:22:55.67,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So Takeshi {\i1}was{\i0} the one who killed Father and Tatsuo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.34,0:22:59.02,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The thud that Conan heard
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.02,0:23:01.45,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,was probably the sound of the killer hitting Tatsuo-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.91,0:23:03.00,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The splash he heard
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.00,0:23:06.94,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,was either the sound of the murder weapon being thrown overboard, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.16,0:23:11.26,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the sound of the killer jumping into the water
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.26,0:23:12.55,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,after running out of places to hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.18,0:23:15.10,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.80,0:23:17.80,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, there's still a high possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.80,0:23:20.04,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,that there's a killer aboard this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.64,0:23:23.72,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all withdraw to the dining room for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.17,0:23:27.58,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying he could be trying to kill me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.03,0:23:29.47,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.47,0:23:33.71,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His motive for murder was to exact revenge on Gozo Hatamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.71,0:23:35.90,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,who drove his father to suicide 10 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.90,0:23:37.93,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But for all we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.67,0:23:43.19,Dialogue,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...he could be trying to kill everyone in the Hatamoto family!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.81,0:24:05.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that you have another man!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.61,0:24:06.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.88,0:24:09.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who wants the inheritance the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.38,0:24:11.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Ichiro was mad at him
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.72,0:24:15.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for tearing up his prize-winning drawing!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.39,0:24:17.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.72,0:24:18.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.66,0:24:21.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my knife...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.39,0:24:22.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}All of these mysteries
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.73,0:24:24.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}are connected by one thread!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.39,0:24:30.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\a6}Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.38,0:24:35.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Sketch book
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.43,0:24:38.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next time will be interesting right from the opening!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.65,0:24:39.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Oh, I'm so excited!
